Title: Series: Venationes Ferarum, Avium, Piscium
Description: Two dragons Decaptitated; groups of men armed with axes, in the foreground and mid ground, have beheaded two dragons, lying upon lettered cloths; in the background, a dragon chases two figures; at the far left, on the other side of the river, an elephant and a dragon fight, before a mountain range Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Jan Collaert II
Curator's comments: See comments to 1957,0413.37. The corners of the margin have been cut (making it difficult to ascertain state); however this impression is recorded in New Hollstein, Johannes Stradanus, as first state.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (517.I) (Johannes Stradanus)
